  "prompt": "What are the best subject combinations to be selected in the arts stream for 11th?",
  "response": "Selecting subjects in the arts stream for 11th grade largely depends on your interests, career aspirations, and academic strengths. Here are some popular and beneficial subject combinations:\n\n1. **History, Political Science, Economics, English**:\n   - Ideal for students interested in careers in civil services, law, politics, and academia.\n\n2. **Psychology, Sociology, History, English**:\n   - Suitable for those looking towards careers in psychology, social work, human resources, and education.\n\n3. **Geography, History, Political Science, English**:\n   - Great for students inclined towards environmental studies, urban planning, and careers in geography and history.\n\n4. **Philosophy, Psychology, Sociology, English**:\n   - Best for students interested in philosophy, mental health, social work, and academia.\n\n5. **Economics, Mathematics, History, English**:\n   - Good for students aiming for careers in economics, business, finance, and academia.\n\n6. **Fine Arts, History, Political Science, English**:\n   - Ideal for students looking to enter the fields of art, design, history, and cultural studies.\n\n7. **Home Science, Sociology, Psychology, English**:\n   - Suitable for careers in nutrition, family counseling, social work, and education.\n\nWhen choosing your subjects, consider the following tips:\n- **Interest and Aptitude**: Select subjects you are genuinely interested in and have an aptitude for.\n- **Career Goals**: Align your subjects with your long-term career goals.\n- **College Requirements**: Research the prerequisites for the courses you may want to pursue in college.\n- **Balanced Workload**: Ensure a balanced workload that you can manage effectively.\n\nRemember to consult with your teachers, career counselors, and parents to make an informed decision.",
